article.description: — John Carter Jr. made four 3-pointers and scored 18 points as Navy got past Lehigh 69-61 on Saturday.
article.headline: Carter leads Navy over Lehigh 69-61 for fifth straight win
article.linkText: Carter leads Navy over Lehigh 69-61 for fifth straight win
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- — John Carter Jr. made four 3-pointers and scored 18 points as Navy got past Lehigh 69-61 on Saturday. Jaylen Walker had 10 points and eight rebounds for Navy (6-1, 3-0 Patriot League), which earned its fifth straight win. Richard Njoku added 10 points as did Cam Davis. Nic Lynch had 17 points and three blocks for the Mountain Hawks (1-2, 1-2). Jalin Sinclair added 14 points. The teams play again Sunday in Annapolis, Maryland. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com ------
